---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<Layout title="Next.js | Skill">
  <Navbar />
  <div class="mt-16 block p-1 md:flex md:justify-center">
    <div class="ml-2 mr-2 md:w-1/2">
      <h1 class="text-center text-3xl font-bold text-text md:text-left">The Node.js Runtime</h1>
      <p class="mb-4 mt-4">
        I use and have used Node.js for a long time, one of the best JavaScript runtimes. I like it
        a lot, especially for its rich ecosystem of available packages. However, today, I am
        focusing on learning the Bun runtime, which is compatible with Node.js, to achieve
        significantly better performance.
      </p>
      <hr />
    </div>
    <div class="hidden w-1/3 justify-end md:flex">
      <img src="https://skillicons.dev/icons?i=nodejs" class="h-40 w-40" />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
